WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
<v Carla>Let's talk openings. Most flat openings have the same problem, and it is not the prose.

2
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.500
It's that nothing is at stake yet. You're describing weather. You're describing a room. The reader is patient but they are not infinitely patient.

3
00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:19.000
My fix is what I call the "tilt". Start a half-second after the world has already tipped. Something is already wrong, or already changing.

4
00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:25.500
You don't open on the calm. You open on the first crack. Readers will forgive almost anything if they feel the tilt.

5
00:00:25.500 --> 00:00:32.000
Concretely: cut your first paragraph. I mean it. Nine times out of ten your real opening is the second paragraph, and the first one was you clearing your throat.

6
00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:38.000
If your opening feels flat, it's usually because you're still on the calm. Find the tilt and start there.
